data.title: Sydney Morning Herald Celebrations - Sydney, New South Wales
data.text:
Nicholas Malanos

We are overjoyed to announce the birth of Nicholas Theodore Malanos, who is positively gorgeous. Nicholas was born 29 April 2024 at St George Private Hospital to very proud parents Theodore and Christina Malanos..

Nicholas is the first grandchild to Nicholas (dec) and Eleni Malanos and to Michael and Mary Fracassi. He is also the first great grandchild to Nina Malanos and Angelo and Maria Colosimo.

Absolutely delighted are Uncles Con and Adam and Aunties Anna, Stephanie and Katherine.

Jack Otis Best Piotrowski

Gorgeous boy Jack was born at 4.10am on April 29, 2024, in Sydney, to mum Jessica Best and dad Daniel Piotrowski.

Jack has already made his family very proud: a first grandchild for Maree and Greg and a second for Sheryl and John.

He is deeply loved by his family including his aunties, uncles, great grandparents, big cousin Francesca and Scout the cat.

A little ray of sunshine has come into the world.

Happy 50-year Anniversary to Jamil and Nabiha Hamka who recently celebrated half a century together on the 02/06/23. Their marriage has blossomed 7 children and going onto 17 grandchildren!

From migrating over from Lebanon in the 70s, they have worked tirelessly to ensure they provide the best possible life for their family. Jamil and Nabiha are both completely selfless individuals who have always put the needs of their friends and family above their own. We all wish them the very best as they celebrate 50 years together and look forward to celebrating many more milestones to come!

Matilda Wood

Joshua and Alice Wood would like to announce the birth of their precious daughter Matilda Ritz Valandian Wood, born 5/5/2023 at 6:06am. She was 3.305kg and 48cm long and has already proven herself to be the most amazingly brave little girl, adored by her grandparents, great-grandparents, aunties and uncles alike. She is our hero.

Our Matilda, make sure everything you do is completely unbelievable - R. Dahl

Edward (Teddy) Tarlinton

Sophie (May) and Tim Tarlinton are delighted to announce that Edward (Teddy) William Tarlinton was born at 10.22 pm on 13th April 2023 weighing in at 4.33kg. First grandchild to Peter and Margie May and one more to Marcia and Andy Tarlinton. We wish them all the very happiest times together.

EVA MCCOMBE

Happy 12th birthday my beautiful little princess.

I want you to know your loving daddy hasn't gone anywhere. I am doing everything to fix the wrong that has been to us and I will keep fighting to give you back the family, friends and life you deserve. Remember, we never give up.

Lots of love your daddy xoxo

(Percival) Charles Ivin and Jennifer Ann Ivin (nee Dinte) will celebrate their 60th Anniversary on the 16th of February 2023.

As longterm Ferny Grove, Brisbane residents who started life in Sydney and spent significant time in Burnie and raised their family in Mackay, they plan to enjoy various small celebrations with their groups of friends and will enjoy time with family who have come from Perth and Sydney.

Both Charles and Jenny continue in their consistent effort of making significant contributions to the environment, industry, research, economy, education, and society (recreational groups, the needy, elderly and youth) through their consistent effort in volunteer, recreational and career roles.

They raised two adult children and played significant roles in the raising of their 4 adult grandchildren. Cathryn Anne and her husband Gary Olsson with their daughter Matilda and son Darcy, and Michael Charles Ivin who has two daughters, Madison and Paige.

Love and Congratulations for this major milestone.

Life's Wot Yer Make It!

Bender Wedding 26-01-2023

Zac Bender (Son of Terry Bender & Helen Warburton) & Hayley Elise Melhuish (Daughter of Douglas Melhuish & Narelle Melhuish nÃ©e Smith) were married on January 26th, 2023 in an intimate Ceremony at Greystone Estate, Pokolbin.

They become the 5th generation to continue their family tradition of an Australia Day Wedding.

The couple would like to thank their Bridal Party of Susan Connolly, Natasha Melhuish, Regan Bender, Thomas Cattle, Shar-lee Clark & Sayyed Ali Qasim.

Thomas and Ana Isabel Cassegrain

are delighted to announce the birth of their first child and daughter

FranÃ§oise-Marie Magdalene Cassegrain

Born on Easter Sunday, the seventeenth of April two thousand and twenty-two at 9:36 in the evening Weighing 8 pounds 6 ounces (3.804 Kg) and measuring 51 centimetres

Thomas and Ana Isabel extend their sincerest gratitude to the doctors, staff and midwives from the Port Macquarie Base Hospital

Parkinson - Hayley & Richard

Congratulations my darling on our 25th wedding anniversary. Thank you for putting up with me and for our wonderful marriage and our 2 wonderful children Julia and Louisa.

Here's Cheers to another 25 years!

With all my love from your loving husband Richard xxx

HAPPY ANNIVERSARY!

Charlotte Airlie Kemp

Courtney and Andrew are delighted to announce the birth of their third child, Charlotte.

Beautiful and serene, Charlotte Airlie Kemp arrived at 3:31pm, Wednesday 16th March 2022 at RPA Birth Centre, Sydney.

Courtney and Andrew would like to thank their midwife, Taylor.

Big sister, Audrey Eleanor, and big brother, Blair William, are very happy and Charlotte's grandparents are joyful.

Courtney's and Andrew's large extended families and many friends have offered their congratulations.

Charlotte is a treasured ray of sunshine and we welcome her to our lives.

Charlotte, may you have good health, happiness and wonderful adventures always.

NICHOLAS

To my darling brother Nick,

Wishing you a wonderful 40th birthday, and all the happiness in the world for this special new decade. I wish I could spend it with you. I love you more than you will ever know, and miss you beyond measure.

Your loving sister, Juliette xox

VIOLET MAE VAN HOORN

20.12.2021

Royal Women's

Hospital, Sydney

2.5kg, 47cm.

Precious daughter to Frances and Ryan, sister to brother Thomas, first granddaughter to Debbie Nankervis, John Lobby Loyde (RIP), niece to Rebecca, Vyvyan and Lucy Lyde, partners Glenn, Alex and Geoff, great niece to Wendy, Dan and family in America and uncle Johnny and Amanda in Melbourne. Granddaughter to Gayle and Bill and extended family in Melbourne.

Perfect baby girl to a loving family, welcome to the world Baby Violet Mae.

Roqueza

Rex and Sinead (nee Byrne) would like to announce the birth of their son Ryan Enrique Roqueza.

Born on Thursday the 16th September 2021 at the Mater Hospital. Welcomed so lovingly by his Mummy and Daddy, big brother Liam, big sister Sophie, grandparents Daniel and Maureen Byrne, Lola Ellen Roqueza and all of his aunties, uncles and cousins.

A very special addition to the Roqueza family who will also be watched over from Heaven by his older brother Noah. Many thanks are extended to Geoff Brieger, as well as the midwives and staff at the Mater.

50th Wedding Anniversary

The children of Alex and Elizabeth (Ryan) Stewart, Kellie and Nathan are pleased to announce the 50th wedding anniversary of their parents on 24 April 2021.

Alex and Liz were married in 1971 at St. Gabrielâs Catholic Church, Bexley, and celebrated with family and friends at Barclay Lounge.

Congratulations on your 50th Wedding Anniversary. With love from all the family.

Byrne

Leona Byrne is delighted to announce the birth of her son Ethan Daniel Byrne, born on the 1st January 2021. Welcomed so lovingly by his Mummy, Grandparents, Daniel & Maureen Byrne, his Aunties, Uncles, Cousins and Leonaâs Friends.

A very special thank you to Leonaâs amazing sister Sinead & Brother in Law, Rex, for their support throughout the pregnancy and beyond.

Thank you to Dr Brieger, Dr Uj & all of the midwives at the Mater Hospital.

Lawton - Gronowski

Mr Darrin Lawton & Mrs Leisa Brown are very pleased to announce the marriage of their daughter Ashlee Mae Rose Lawton to Daniel Joseph Gronowski. Ashlee and Daniel were married on Saturday 31st October 2020 at the Royal Botanic Gardens, Bennelong Lawn in Sydney.

Renowned Celebrant Jessie Cacchillo officiated the intimate ceremony. Ashlee was wearing an Australian designed Ivory Organza Gown with a full length Pearl Veil. Ashlee walked down the aisle to the soothing sounds of âSomewhere over the rainbowâ played live by the String Space Quartet, escorted by her parents, brother Danaan Lawton and bridesmaids Mikhayla Mar, Lauren Payne and Clare Tolkien, wearing Fluted Ivory midi dresses.

Daniel is the son of Stefan Gronowski and Sue Gronowski . He and his attending Groomsmen Tony and Jon Gronowski, Tommy Rodrigues and Jayme Payne were dressed in traditional Black and White Tuxedos.

The ceremony was followed by a Dinner Party celebration, with live jazz and champagne in the Ballroom of The Langham Sydney, where Master of Ceremonies Tommy Rodrigues introduced the newly married Mr & Mrs Gronowski to their dearest family and friends.

Alice Carr

Carr (Burke)

Caroline and Nick are delighted to announce the birth of their daughter ALICE BELINDA who was born on Friday September 13 2019.

A very welcome sister for Robbie and Hamish

Nazanin Mondschein

Happy birthday to this amazing woman! Therapist to friends & family, fearless mother of 2 rascals, & wife to a man who forgets everything (except her & her beautiful soul).

We love you eleven & more.

Alice Brewer & Drew Wrigley

Ross and Janice Brewer of Lambs Valley, NSW, are thrilled to announce the engagement of their younger daughter, Alice, to Drew Wrigley, youngest son of Peter and Sue Wrigley of Drummoyne. Both families wish them much joy and happiness as they plan their future together.

Xuelian Teng & Michael Ramage

Michael P Ramage and Xuelian Teng are engaged to be married. Michael and Xuelian became engaged on the 29th of December in Beijing 2018.

Michael son of Peter John Ramage and Nancy Ruth Ramage (deceased) of Eastwood Sydney Australia and Xuelian daughter of Tang Peng Teng and Qing Mei Han of Shandong China.

Further details of the wedding will be announced in due course.
